00:00:12.250 --> 00:00:19.130 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.130 --> 00:00:22.100 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Mona Sobhani
says, scientific materialism

00:00:22.100 --> 00:00:24.690 align:middle line:10%
can no longer be the
standard of science.

00:00:24.690 --> 00:00:26.690 align:middle line:10%
It's been proved beyond
a shadow of a doubt

00:00:26.690 --> 00:00:29.330 align:middle line:10%
that the unseen quantum
world of intelligence

00:00:29.330 --> 00:00:33.300 align:middle line:10%
has to be included in scientific
discovery, starting now.

00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:35.690 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, Mona's journey
was a difficult one

00:00:35.690 --> 00:00:38.630 align:middle line:84%
because it pitted her
mind against her intuition

00:00:38.630 --> 00:00:39.870 align:middle line:90%
as a scientist.

00:00:39.870 --> 00:00:42.470 align:middle line:84%
And so this is going to be a
wonderful conversation for those

00:00:42.470 --> 00:00:45.480 align:middle line:84%
of you who know doubters
or are doubters yourself.

00:00:45.480 --> 00:00:46.617 align:middle line:90%
So, Mona, welcome.

00:00:46.617 --> 00:00:47.700 align:middle line:90%
I've never met you before.

00:00:47.700 --> 00:00:48.658 align:middle line:90%
This is the first time.

00:00:48.658 --> 00:00:49.810 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to Open Minds.

00:00:49.810 --> 00:00:51.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MONA SOBHANI: Thank you
so much for having me.

00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:53.393 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you
took a brave journey

00:00:53.393 --> 00:00:55.350 align:middle line:84%
because you're from
a Persian family.

00:00:55.350 --> 00:00:58.110 align:middle line:84%
And so it's-- we were
talking off camera.

00:00:58.110 --> 00:01:00.320 align:middle line:84%
I said, were you always
a little sciencey kid?

00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:02.750 align:middle line:84%
Because you took this
all, and you said, no.

00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:06.460 align:middle line:10%
>>SOBHANI: Mm-mm, science
was my worst subject,

00:01:06.460 --> 00:01:09.110 align:middle line:10%
those standardized tests
that you take every year.

00:01:09.110 --> 00:01:12.560 align:middle line:10%
I had, like, the highest
percentile for every subject.

00:01:12.560 --> 00:01:15.650 align:middle line:84%
And then science would
be like 70 out of 100.

00:01:15.650 --> 00:01:18.760 align:middle line:10%
And it was mostly because I just
wasn't interested in the science

00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:20.080 align:middle line:10%
that they were teaching us.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:23.287 align:middle line:10%
It'd be like geology or weather
patterns or whatever it was,

00:01:23.287 --> 00:01:24.620 align:middle line:10%
and I wasn't interested in that.

00:01:24.620 --> 00:01:29.180 align:middle line:10%
So it wasn't until I found
neuroscience in, I think,

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:30.890 align:middle line:10%
my 12th grade--

00:01:30.890 --> 00:01:33.910 align:middle line:10%
I think it was 12th grade when
I started to get interested

00:01:33.910 --> 00:01:35.000 align:middle line:10%
in science, actually.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:36.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah
started lighting up.

00:01:36.460 --> 00:01:39.490 align:middle line:84%
Well, so even though your
family, which is your

00:01:39.490 --> 00:01:42.230 align:middle line:84%
to be successful, you
need a good career path.

00:01:42.230 --> 00:01:43.930 align:middle line:84%
You choose science,
not art, right?

00:01:43.930 --> 00:01:44.300 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yes.

00:01:44.300 --> 00:01:45.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or literature.

00:01:45.050 --> 00:01:46.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, and
I'm Persian, so it's--

00:01:46.970 --> 00:01:48.620 align:middle line:90%
we're either lawyers or doctors.

00:01:48.620 --> 00:01:49.640 align:middle line:90%
That's the choice.

00:01:49.640 --> 00:01:51.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so you
chose the doctor path.

00:01:51.930 --> 00:01:52.730 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:01:52.730 --> 00:01:54.670 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: But what's
interesting to me

00:01:54.670 --> 00:01:57.320 align:middle line:10%
in reading about you
is that your mother,

00:01:57.320 --> 00:02:01.780 align:middle line:10%
the matrilineal part of your
family were very intuitive

00:02:01.780 --> 00:02:05.450 align:middle line:10%
and used old school practices
with their intuition.

00:02:05.450 --> 00:02:09.340 align:middle line:84%
So bring us into that world
of coffee ground readings

00:02:09.340 --> 00:02:10.930 align:middle line:90%
from grandma and your mom.

00:02:10.930 --> 00:02:13.340 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yes,
so in our culture,

00:02:13.340 --> 00:02:14.810 align:middle line:90%
we're actually very mystical.

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:17.450 align:middle line:84%
The history of the Persian
lineage is very mystical,

00:02:17.450 --> 00:02:21.020 align:middle line:84%
and one of the traditions that
was passed down was divination.

00:02:21.020 --> 00:02:23.230 align:middle line:84%
My grandmother, the
way that she practiced

00:02:23.230 --> 00:02:26.450 align:middle line:84%
that was using coffee grinds,
like, not American coffee,

00:02:26.450 --> 00:02:29.080 align:middle line:84%
like thicker Turkish,
Armenian, Greek coffee.

00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:29.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you
grind it like that.

00:02:29.930 --> 00:02:31.805 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, and
you leave it in the cup,

00:02:31.805 --> 00:02:32.810 align:middle line:90%
so it creates pictures.

00:02:32.810 --> 00:02:36.760 align:middle line:84%
So then, the reader looks at
the pictures and intuits things

00:02:36.760 --> 00:02:38.960 align:middle line:84%
about the person's life
past, present, or future.

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:41.760 align:middle line:84%
So my grandma used to do
this, and she taught my mom

00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:42.560 align:middle line:90%
how to do it.

00:02:42.560 --> 00:02:43.977 align:middle line:84%
She tried to teach
the other kids,

00:02:43.977 --> 00:02:46.160 align:middle line:84%
but they weren't
as good as my mom.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:50.628 align:middle line:84%
So my mom started doing it for
our family friends at parties,

00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:52.670 align:middle line:84%
and I never noticed it
because I grew up with it.

00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:54.590 align:middle line:84%
So it was very in
the background.

00:02:54.590 --> 00:02:55.900 align:middle line:90%
And obviously, I was a kid.

00:02:55.900 --> 00:02:58.273 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't drinking coffee,
so I didn't notice it.

00:02:58.273 --> 00:02:59.940 align:middle line:84%
But when I started
going to grad school,

00:02:59.940 --> 00:03:01.440 align:middle line:84%
and I would go home
on the weekends,

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:04.260 align:middle line:84%
she would make me coffee,
and then absentmindedly,

00:03:04.260 --> 00:03:06.190 align:middle line:84%
like, turn it over and
just start reading.

00:03:06.190 --> 00:03:08.890 align:middle line:84%
And I was in graduate
school for neuroscience.

00:03:08.890 --> 00:03:09.880 align:middle line:90%
So I was--

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:10.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mom.

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:12.420 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah,
I'm a scientist.

00:03:12.420 --> 00:03:13.420 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe in this.

00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:17.440 align:middle line:84%
But she would say things,
and I would just listen,

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:19.960 align:middle line:90%
and then I would take notes.

00:03:19.960 --> 00:03:23.250 align:middle line:84%
And over time, I
noticed that she

00:03:23.250 --> 00:03:24.640 align:middle line:84%
would get a lot
of details right,

00:03:24.640 --> 00:03:27.720 align:middle line:84%
and things that she would
say would come true weeks

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:28.870 align:middle line:90%
in advance.

00:03:28.870 --> 00:03:31.750 align:middle line:84%
They would pan out over
weeks, sometimes even months.

00:03:31.750 --> 00:03:35.123 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of times they would be
things that I couldn't possibly

00:03:35.123 --> 00:03:36.040 align:middle line:90%
know they were coming.

00:03:36.040 --> 00:03:38.190 align:middle line:90%
She couldn't possibly know.

00:03:38.190 --> 00:03:40.740 align:middle line:84%
So it was the
number of variables

00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:44.220 align:middle line:84%
that she would get correct,
the small, meaningful details

00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:46.932 align:middle line:84%
that nobody in my
life would know,

00:03:46.932 --> 00:03:48.640 align:middle line:84%
things that I would
just think in my head

00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:49.680 align:middle line:84%
but that were very
meaningful to.

00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:50.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That were
coming out the ground.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:52.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, she
would say them out loud,

00:03:52.110 --> 00:03:54.660 align:middle line:84%
and I would just sit
there, and sometimes there

00:03:54.660 --> 00:03:56.950 align:middle line:84%
were things I would not
want my mom to know.

00:03:56.950 --> 00:03:58.930 align:middle line:84%
Like, I would
purposely not tell her.

00:03:58.930 --> 00:04:00.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You can't keep
secrets from that kind of mom.

00:04:00.360 --> 00:04:01.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: So yeah, you--

00:04:01.320 --> 00:04:02.550 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, yeah,
I would not want

00:04:02.550 --> 00:04:04.092 align:middle line:84%
to have coffee
because I'd be like, I

00:04:04.092 --> 00:04:06.147 align:middle line:90%
don't her to want to know.

00:04:06.147 --> 00:04:07.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Was just spying on me.

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:11.080 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, so I couldn't
explain it with science.

00:04:11.080 --> 00:04:13.050 align:middle line:84%
So I just lived in
cognitive dissonance

00:04:13.050 --> 00:04:16.950 align:middle line:84%
and kind of ignored it
because I couldn't really

00:04:16.950 --> 00:04:18.602 align:middle line:90%
reconcile the two worlds.

00:04:18.602 --> 00:04:20.310 align:middle line:84%
But I came to count
on it because she was

00:04:20.310 --> 00:04:21.610 align:middle line:90%
more right than she was wrong.

00:04:21.610 --> 00:04:22.783 align:middle line:90%
So I knew it worked.

00:04:22.783 --> 00:04:23.950 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know how it worked.

00:04:23.950 --> 00:04:27.010 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know why,
but it was useful.

00:04:27.010 --> 00:04:30.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And as I
recall, you kept a diary

00:04:30.480 --> 00:04:32.110 align:middle line:90%
for 10 years of those readings.

00:04:32.110 --> 00:04:32.910 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yes.

00:04:32.910 --> 00:04:35.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So at what point did
you start taking her seriously

00:04:35.620 --> 00:04:37.720 align:middle line:84%
and start writing down
what she had told you?

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:39.600 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: So my
friends would fight over

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:41.595 align:middle line:84%
who could come over on
Sundays to get readings.

00:04:41.595 --> 00:04:42.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, because
they all wanted readings?

00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:43.630 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, they
all wanted readings.

00:04:43.630 --> 00:04:45.735 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, how old
were you by this time?

00:04:45.735 --> 00:04:47.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: I was
in my early 20s.

00:04:47.110 --> 00:04:47.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:04:47.460 --> 00:04:48.297 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:04:48.297 --> 00:04:49.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Young adult, OK.

00:04:49.380 --> 00:04:52.067 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah,
we were, I think

00:04:52.067 --> 00:04:53.400 align:middle line:90%
that's when I started to notice.

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:54.350 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, well,
my friends really

00:04:54.350 --> 00:04:55.620 align:middle line:84%
want to come over
for these readings.

00:04:55.620 --> 00:04:57.620 align:middle line:84%
Like, maybe I should pay
more attention to them.

00:04:57.620 --> 00:05:00.840 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's when
I started taking notes.

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:03.320 align:middle line:84%
I mean, also, I would forget
things that she would say,

00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:06.710 align:middle line:84%
and then it would become hard to
be like, is that what she said?

00:05:06.710 --> 00:05:08.310 align:middle line:90%
My memory is not reliable?

00:05:08.310 --> 00:05:10.188 align:middle line:84%
So I was like, well,
if I want to be--

00:05:10.188 --> 00:05:11.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm in grad school
to be a scientist.

00:05:11.730 --> 00:05:13.280 align:middle line:90%
I should be taking notes.

00:05:13.280 --> 00:05:15.000 align:middle line:84%
So that's why I
started taking notes.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, I tracked
it for over 10 years.

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:20.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, anytime she reads for
me, I'll jot down what she says,

00:05:20.370 --> 00:05:21.502 align:middle line:90%
if I think it's--

00:05:21.502 --> 00:05:22.710 align:middle line:90%
which that's the funny thing.

00:05:22.710 --> 00:05:24.360 align:middle line:90%
I should have learned by now.

00:05:24.360 --> 00:05:27.360 align:middle line:84%
It's not always what
I think is important.

00:05:27.360 --> 00:05:28.768 align:middle line:90%
It's usually-- yeah, it's--

00:05:28.768 --> 00:05:30.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's something
trying to come out

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.360 align:middle line:84%
in a message for
you, and you just

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:33.527 align:middle line:90%
are dismissing it sometimes.

00:05:33.527 --> 00:05:34.327 align:middle line:90%
We do that.

00:05:34.327 --> 00:05:35.360 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Definitely.

00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:35.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:05:35.820 --> 00:05:37.340 align:middle line:84%
So I'd like to get
into the nature

00:05:37.340 --> 00:05:40.080 align:middle line:84%
of a couple of the readings
that really kind of rocked you.

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:41.640 align:middle line:90%
And it is interesting.

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:44.070 align:middle line:84%
We all still when we
have these experiences,

00:05:44.070 --> 00:05:45.990 align:middle line:90%
we think, how is this possible?

00:05:45.990 --> 00:05:48.660 align:middle line:84%
Still, even those who are
experienced in this realm.

00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:51.200 align:middle line:84%
So one of them had
to do, your mom

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:55.760 align:middle line:84%
saw a man with beautiful,
long eyelashes.

00:05:55.760 --> 00:06:00.380 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yes, so this was one
of the moments, I think, where--

00:06:00.380 --> 00:06:02.280 align:middle line:90%
so I was dating somebody.

00:06:02.280 --> 00:06:05.810 align:middle line:90%
It was in my mid, early 20s.

00:06:05.810 --> 00:06:08.970 align:middle line:84%
Dating this guy, and
I remember-- to me,

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:09.900 align:middle line:90%
I loved his lashes.

00:06:09.900 --> 00:06:11.340 align:middle line:84%
They were very
long and beautiful,

00:06:11.340 --> 00:06:13.507 align:middle line:84%
but it was not something I
said out loud to anybody.

00:06:13.507 --> 00:06:15.830 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't a common
feature I always

00:06:15.830 --> 00:06:18.540 align:middle line:84%
liked in the guys I
was dating or anything.

00:06:18.540 --> 00:06:21.080 align:middle line:90%
It was just him specifically.

00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:22.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Unique to him.

00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:24.180 align:middle line:90%
But weren't you also--

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:27.380 align:middle line:84%
as I recall, in
your culture, you

00:06:27.380 --> 00:06:29.930 align:middle line:84%
don't just go talking about
someone you went on a first date

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:30.300 align:middle line:90%
with.

00:06:30.300 --> 00:06:31.650 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Oh, yeah, I
would never tell my mom.

00:06:31.650 --> 00:06:32.720 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have
to-- you have to wait

00:06:32.720 --> 00:06:35.700 align:middle line:84%
until it's very serious before
you would even mention anyone.

00:06:35.700 --> 00:06:36.700 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: That's right.

00:06:36.700 --> 00:06:40.440 align:middle line:84%
Our culture takes, I guess,
dating very seriously.

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:42.810 align:middle line:84%
And my parents,
especially my mom,

00:06:42.810 --> 00:06:45.300 align:middle line:84%
is pretty old-school,
so I wasn't though.

00:06:45.300 --> 00:06:47.300 align:middle line:84%
So I was just living my
life the way I wanted to

00:06:47.300 --> 00:06:49.460 align:middle line:84%
and I just wouldn't
tell her anything.

00:06:49.460 --> 00:06:50.970 align:middle line:84%
So when she would
do the readings,

00:06:50.970 --> 00:06:52.260 align:middle line:84%
that's what I was
referring to earlier.

00:06:52.260 --> 00:06:54.718 align:middle line:84%
Like things I wouldn't want
her to know or things like that

00:06:54.718 --> 00:06:57.900 align:middle line:84%
where she would see things and
I just wouldn't say anything.

00:06:57.900 --> 00:07:00.630 align:middle line:84%
She'd be like, well, it looks
like there's a guy in your life.

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:01.790 align:middle line:84%
And that would just
sit there quietly.

00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:02.707 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Turning red.

00:07:02.707 --> 00:07:06.672 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yes, and then so
for this guy she mentioned,

00:07:06.672 --> 00:07:08.630 align:middle line:84%
she's like, oh, and it
looks like he has really

00:07:08.630 --> 00:07:09.990 align:middle line:90%
long, beautiful eyelashes.

00:07:09.990 --> 00:07:13.310 align:middle line:84%
And every time that she would
do a reading, he would show up

00:07:13.310 --> 00:07:14.960 align:middle line:90%
and she would mention the--

00:07:14.960 --> 00:07:16.640 align:middle line:90%
he became the lash guy.

00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:20.720 align:middle line:84%
And it was what it shook me
though the first time because it

00:07:20.720 --> 00:07:23.760 align:middle line:84%
was just a thought that I had
never said out loud to anybody,

00:07:23.760 --> 00:07:25.140 align:middle line:90%
I hadn't told anybody.

00:07:25.140 --> 00:07:25.950 align:middle line:90%
It was so weird.

00:07:25.950 --> 00:07:28.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there were obviously
other things I liked about him.

00:07:28.450 --> 00:07:30.680 align:middle line:84%
So it was kind of
interesting that

00:07:30.680 --> 00:07:33.390 align:middle line:84%
was like the meaningful
detail that she picked up on,

00:07:33.390 --> 00:07:35.430 align:middle line:84%
and it became this thing
that represented him.

00:07:35.430 --> 00:07:37.760 align:middle line:84%
And that was something
I couldn't understand

00:07:37.760 --> 00:07:41.600 align:middle line:84%
from a science perspective,
but that deeply intrigued me

00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:42.588 align:middle line:90%
about the readings.

00:07:42.588 --> 00:07:44.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, oh,
I'm sure it would.

00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:46.970 align:middle line:84%
You start getting into all kinds
of entanglement theory by then.

00:07:46.970 --> 00:07:47.210 align:middle line:90%
All right?

00:07:47.210 --> 00:07:47.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:07:47.330 --> 00:07:49.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, and another
one she was telling you,

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:52.160 align:middle line:84%
which I mean, it sounds
like a Gypsy fortune teller.

00:07:52.160 --> 00:07:54.200 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
get very bad news.

00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:57.110 align:middle line:84%
But she didn't say this
like a Gypsy fortune teller.

00:07:57.110 --> 00:08:00.290 align:middle line:84%
She was very sincere in
trying to give you a heads up.

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:03.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, so she
didn't usually give bad news.

00:08:03.740 --> 00:08:06.250 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, but it was--

00:08:06.250 --> 00:08:07.820 align:middle line:90%
I think it was 2016.

00:08:07.820 --> 00:08:10.873 align:middle line:84%
And for a few weeks, she
was seeing something,

00:08:10.873 --> 00:08:12.290 align:middle line:84%
and she would get
kind of awkward.

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:16.070 align:middle line:84%
And then, finally, she said,
I don't want to scare you,

00:08:16.070 --> 00:08:19.330 align:middle line:84%
but I feel like I should warn
you that because I've seen it

00:08:19.330 --> 00:08:21.400 align:middle line:84%
for a few weeks in
a row that you're

00:08:21.400 --> 00:08:24.100 align:middle line:84%
going to get some
bad news, and that

00:08:24.100 --> 00:08:27.110 align:middle line:84%
shook me because my mom
never said things like that.

00:08:27.110 --> 00:08:28.850 align:middle line:84%
And so I was like,
what do you mean?

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:30.380 align:middle line:84%
I tried to get more
information out of her,

00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:31.838 align:middle line:84%
but she wouldn't
say anything else.

00:08:31.838 --> 00:08:34.400 align:middle line:84%
She was like, I don't really
know what I'm looking at,

00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:37.010 align:middle line:90%
and I don't want to--

00:08:37.010 --> 00:08:38.260 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Program, yeah, yeah.

00:08:38.260 --> 00:08:41.335 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, and put
it in your head, and what

00:08:41.335 --> 00:08:42.710 align:middle line:84%
if it doesn't
happen or whatever.

00:08:42.710 --> 00:08:44.500 align:middle line:84%
So she's like, just
keep that in mind.

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:46.110 align:middle line:90%
So for six weeks--

00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:48.960 align:middle line:84%
and I told you, by this
point, I trusted her.

00:08:48.960 --> 00:08:50.010 align:middle line:90%
Like, I knew--

00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:52.750 align:middle line:84%
I felt like it's possible
something could happen.

00:08:52.750 --> 00:08:54.180 align:middle line:84%
So for six weeks,
I kind of lived

00:08:54.180 --> 00:08:56.100 align:middle line:84%
in this very anxious
state of like, who

00:08:56.100 --> 00:08:57.550 align:middle line:90%
is going to give me bad news?

00:08:57.550 --> 00:08:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And I would ask my
friends who has bad news.

00:08:59.860 --> 00:09:02.100 align:middle line:90%
And I tried to get ahead of it.

00:09:02.100 --> 00:09:02.950 align:middle line:90%
Of course, I didn't.

00:09:02.950 --> 00:09:05.460 align:middle line:84%
But six weeks later,
I got a message

00:09:05.460 --> 00:09:07.870 align:middle line:84%
from one of my classmates
that-- they're like,

00:09:07.870 --> 00:09:09.280 align:middle line:90%
have you heard the news?

00:09:09.280 --> 00:09:10.330 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, I knew it.

00:09:10.330 --> 00:09:11.130 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:09:11.130 --> 00:09:13.560 align:middle line:84%
And one of our
professors at USC was

00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:16.300 align:middle line:84%
killed by one of the
students in the program,

00:09:16.300 --> 00:09:18.930 align:middle line:84%
and it was somebody who had
worked on one of my dissertation

00:09:18.930 --> 00:09:19.730 align:middle line:90%
experiments.

00:09:19.730 --> 00:09:20.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He was close to you.

00:09:20.490 --> 00:09:21.532 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: With me, yeah.

00:09:21.532 --> 00:09:24.310 align:middle line:84%
So it was very
upsetting, obviously,

00:09:24.310 --> 00:09:27.490 align:middle line:84%
for the whole community
and for me personally.

00:09:27.490 --> 00:09:30.670 align:middle line:84%
And so I told my mom I was
like, I think I know what it is.

00:09:30.670 --> 00:09:31.630 align:middle line:90%
I think it's this.

00:09:31.630 --> 00:09:33.700 align:middle line:90%
And she said, Yeah.

00:09:33.700 --> 00:09:35.710 align:middle line:84%
So then, she's like,
I knew it was a death.

00:09:35.710 --> 00:09:36.720 align:middle line:90%
It looked like a death.

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.490 align:middle line:84%
She was like, I didn't
want to tell you,

00:09:38.490 --> 00:09:41.060 align:middle line:90%
why get upset beforehand?

00:09:41.060 --> 00:09:42.667 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You go
looking for things.

00:09:42.667 --> 00:09:44.250 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Right,
and she's like-- she

00:09:44.250 --> 00:09:45.792 align:middle line:84%
said she had also
never seen anything

00:09:45.792 --> 00:09:48.420 align:middle line:84%
like it, which is
interesting because it

00:09:48.420 --> 00:09:49.740 align:middle line:90%
was an unusual circumstance.

00:09:49.740 --> 00:09:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: For a student
to kill a professor.

00:09:51.100 --> 00:09:51.900 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:09:51.900 --> 00:09:53.040 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, so
she's like, I just

00:09:53.040 --> 00:09:54.370 align:middle line:90%
had not seen anything like it.

00:09:54.370 --> 00:09:56.590 align:middle line:84%
And she's like, so I
didn't know what it meant.

00:09:56.590 --> 00:09:57.030 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:09:57.030 --> 00:09:57.285 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:09:57.285 --> 00:09:59.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So then, we
go on, and then we'll

00:09:59.220 --> 00:10:02.080 align:middle line:90%
wrap this phase up about mom.

00:10:02.080 --> 00:10:05.790 align:middle line:84%
But then, mom saw
a romance for you.

00:10:05.790 --> 00:10:08.640 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Right, so
that event with the death

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:11.130 align:middle line:84%
shook me because also
suddenly the readings were

00:10:11.130 --> 00:10:14.740 align:middle line:84%
about life and death, which
before this, they were not.

00:10:14.740 --> 00:10:17.863 align:middle line:84%
And so that kind of
shook me and made

00:10:17.863 --> 00:10:19.030 align:middle line:90%
me think about the universe.

00:10:19.030 --> 00:10:22.912 align:middle line:84%
And is there something that
exists like fate or destiny?

00:10:22.912 --> 00:10:24.870 align:middle line:84%
Because how could the
information of your death

00:10:24.870 --> 00:10:27.570 align:middle line:84%
be available in the
ethers ahead of time?

00:10:27.570 --> 00:10:29.410 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't do
anything with that.

00:10:29.410 --> 00:10:31.540 align:middle line:90%
I just kind of it scared me.

00:10:31.540 --> 00:10:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And then, I went
on with my life.

00:10:33.580 --> 00:10:36.280 align:middle line:84%
But then, if you-- it was
a couple of years later,

00:10:36.280 --> 00:10:39.255 align:middle line:84%
I got in this relationship,
and I was like,

00:10:39.255 --> 00:10:41.130 align:middle line:90%
oh, I'm going to be happy now.

00:10:41.130 --> 00:10:42.140 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:10:42.140 --> 00:10:43.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And she
told you you're

00:10:43.040 --> 00:10:44.220 align:middle line:90%
going to be in a relationship.

00:10:44.220 --> 00:10:44.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, and
she had seen that.

00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:46.677 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And she said
it would be a good one.

00:10:46.677 --> 00:10:48.920 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, she said,
and it was a good one.

00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:50.610 align:middle line:90%
And she saw all these details.

00:10:50.610 --> 00:10:53.600 align:middle line:84%
Everything was correct,
again, all the creepy details.

00:10:53.600 --> 00:10:56.750 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have eyelashes, but
she got other details about him

00:10:56.750 --> 00:10:59.040 align:middle line:84%
correct that were
very specific to him.

00:10:59.040 --> 00:11:02.060 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, she was
like, it'll be good.

00:11:02.060 --> 00:11:02.940 align:middle line:90%
But then it ended.

00:11:02.940 --> 00:11:04.315 align:middle line:84%
So then, to me,
that wasn't good.

00:11:04.315 --> 00:11:04.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:11:04.730 --> 00:11:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And so then it made you
start doubting things

00:11:06.650 --> 00:11:08.845 align:middle line:90%
and put you into a dark place.

00:11:08.845 --> 00:11:11.865 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: It made me just
feel confused, I think.

00:11:11.865 --> 00:11:13.730 align:middle line:90%
Yes, definitely dark.

00:11:13.730 --> 00:11:16.280 align:middle line:84%
There were a lot of
things, I think, in my life

00:11:16.280 --> 00:11:17.850 align:middle line:90%
falling apart at that time.

00:11:17.850 --> 00:11:20.090 align:middle line:84%
It was one of those
eras where everything

00:11:20.090 --> 00:11:21.142 align:middle line:90%
started to deconstruct.

00:11:21.142 --> 00:11:22.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What was happening?

00:11:22.350 --> 00:11:24.935 align:middle line:84%
By the way, what was happening
in your professional life?

00:11:24.935 --> 00:11:29.420 align:middle line:10%
>>SOBHANI: So I had a new
job that I had started,

00:11:29.420 --> 00:11:33.780 align:middle line:10%
but I had hit the workforce
after getting my PhD.

00:11:33.780 --> 00:11:36.560 align:middle line:84%
And I started having a bit
of an existential crisis

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:38.770 align:middle line:84%
because every morning,
I would wake up

00:11:38.770 --> 00:11:40.220 align:middle line:90%
and think, oh no, is this it.

00:11:40.220 --> 00:11:42.410 align:middle line:10%
This is what we do
forever until we die.

00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:44.800 align:middle line:84%
We just go to work and have
no time to do anything.

00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:47.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What were you doing
day by day in your work?

00:11:47.050 --> 00:11:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: I was working at
a Research Center at USC.

00:11:50.240 --> 00:11:54.140 align:middle line:84%
So I was running operations
and running the studies.

00:11:54.140 --> 00:11:57.280 align:middle line:84%
So it was a very,
very demanding job.

00:11:57.280 --> 00:12:00.080 align:middle line:10%
And I was working
a lot of hours.

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:01.900 align:middle line:84%
So that's why I think
I was thinking--

00:12:01.900 --> 00:12:03.525 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In the
field of neuroscience?

00:12:03.525 --> 00:12:06.500 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah, it was
neuroscience and digital health.

00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:08.570 align:middle line:84%
And so it was just
very demanding.

00:12:08.570 --> 00:12:09.370 align:middle line:90%
And I started to--

00:12:09.370 --> 00:12:11.695 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Repetitious,
probably, a bit of that?

00:12:11.695 --> 00:12:13.905 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Actually,
it was not repetitious.

00:12:13.905 --> 00:12:14.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's good.

00:12:14.920 --> 00:12:17.045 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Actually,
every day was a new thing.

00:12:17.045 --> 00:12:18.420 align:middle line:84%
But that also has
its challenges.

00:12:18.420 --> 00:12:19.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, OK.

00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:20.080 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:12:20.080 --> 00:12:21.800 align:middle line:84%
You have to figure
things out every day.

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:23.670 align:middle line:90%
So it was a lot.

00:12:23.670 --> 00:12:24.470 align:middle line:90%
It was a lot.

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:28.340 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, I just started to have
an existential crisis, I think.

00:12:28.340 --> 00:12:33.700 align:middle line:84%
And then all of those, the death
and the relationship ending

00:12:33.700 --> 00:12:36.040 align:middle line:84%
and then a few other
things, I just fell.

00:12:36.040 --> 00:12:38.630 align:middle line:84%
And the relationship
was the final--

00:12:38.630 --> 00:12:42.650 align:middle line:84%
I was like, I give up, and I
just fell into a depression.

00:12:42.650 --> 00:12:43.450 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:45.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you
continued with your job

00:12:45.730 --> 00:12:48.740 align:middle line:84%
but just struggled in your
personal life then for a while?

00:12:48.740 --> 00:12:49.540 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:12:49.540 --> 00:12:50.920 align:middle line:90%
I was like a zombie.

00:12:50.920 --> 00:12:52.430 align:middle line:84%
I don't know where
I went mentally,

00:12:52.430 --> 00:12:53.430 align:middle line:90%
but I was never present.

00:12:53.430 --> 00:12:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But this question
lingered, thinking back

00:12:56.800 --> 00:12:59.440 align:middle line:84%
on what happened to the
Professor, foretold of six weeks

00:12:59.440 --> 00:13:04.540 align:middle line:84%
before it happened, about free
will and destiny and mind.

00:13:04.540 --> 00:13:09.405 align:middle line:84%
And this became a real
area of seeking for you.

00:13:09.405 --> 00:13:10.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yes.

00:13:10.810 --> 00:13:13.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Just launch
in and tell us all about

00:13:13.120 --> 00:13:14.570 align:middle line:90%
that because this is a big one.

00:13:14.570 --> 00:13:15.370 align:middle line:90%
>>SOBHANI: Yeah.

00:13:15.370 --> 00:13:23.540 align:middle line:84%
So after I was in this dark
space for a few months,

00:13:23.540 --> 00:13:27.430 align:middle line:84%
I started to come
out and my mind

00:13:27.430 --> 00:13:28.630 align:middle line:90%
started to come back online.

00:13:28.630 --> 00:13:31.995 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking about the
coffee because I was confused.

00:13:31.995 --> 00:13:34.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, sometimes it was
right, sometimes it was wrong.

00:13:34.370 --> 00:13:38.760 align:middle line:84%
Or the interpretation,
what matters, or maybe I

00:13:38.760 --> 00:13:40.270 align:middle line:90%
was making it up all along.

00:13:40.270 --> 00:13:42.430 align:middle line:84%
And neuroscience and
science is right.

00:13:42.430 --> 00:13:44.310 align:middle line:90%
We create meaning in our minds.

00:13:44.310 --> 00:13:47.380 align:middle line:90%
So I decided to start exploring.

00:13:47.380 --> 00:13:51.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think it wasn't
even my decision at first.

00:13:51.160 --> 00:13:52.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm from Los Angeles.

00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:56.430 align:middle line:84%
So I had a group of girlfriends
that I grew up with.

00:13:56.430 --> 00:13:59.730 align:middle line:84%
And we know of a
really good psychic.

00:13:59.730 --> 00:14:02.222 align:middle line:84%
And she'll turn you away If
she can't read your energy.

00:14:02.222 --> 00:14:03.555 align:middle line:90%
She turned my friend away twice.

00:14:03.555 --> 00:14:05.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because you didn't
want to go to your mom for this.

00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:07.918 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: Well, I wanted
to try something different.

00:14:07.918 --> 00:14:09.600 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I got you.

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:12.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: I wanted
to explore the space

00:14:12.360 --> 00:14:14.230 align:middle line:84%
and see how it was
for other people.

00:14:14.230 --> 00:14:16.960 align:middle line:84%
And so we went to
do these readings.

00:14:16.960 --> 00:14:20.160 align:middle line:84%
And it was really fascinating
because they were much more

00:14:20.160 --> 00:14:23.370 align:middle line:90%
detailed than my mom.

00:14:23.370 --> 00:14:26.200 align:middle line:84%
But they were each
good in their own ways.

00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:27.640 align:middle line:90%
But they were very detailed.

00:14:27.640 --> 00:14:30.400 align:middle line:84%
And I, of course, recorded
them and took notes.

00:14:30.400 --> 00:14:33.040 align:middle line:84%
And they got so many
variables right, again,

00:14:33.040 --> 00:14:36.520 align:middle line:84%
for each event that I
just didn't understand

00:14:36.520 --> 00:14:37.730 align:middle line:90%
how it could be possible.

00:14:37.730 --> 00:14:39.770 align:middle line:90%
So they blew my mind.

00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:42.460 align:middle line:84%
And that launched me
on a personal project

00:14:42.460 --> 00:14:47.800 align:middle line:84%
to interview these intuitives
because I started to wonder.

00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:49.370 align:middle line:90%
Let's say, it's true.

00:14:49.370 --> 00:14:53.740 align:middle line:84%
Let's say, they're picking
up on a signal or something.

00:14:53.740 --> 00:14:55.710 align:middle line:90%
What is perceiving the signal?

00:14:55.710 --> 00:14:56.510 align:middle line:90%
Is it the brain?

00:14:56.510 --> 00:14:59.080 align:middle line:84%
And if it's the brain,
what part of the brain

00:14:59.080 --> 00:15:01.160 align:middle line:84%
and what makes them
special and different?

00:15:01.160 --> 00:15:03.980 align:middle line:84%
So I started to go into
science mode about it.

00:15:03.980 --> 00:15:06.640 align:middle line:84%
But I was really interested
in just talking to them

00:15:06.640 --> 00:15:10.010 align:middle line:84%
about their experience of it
because when they do readings,

00:15:10.010 --> 00:15:12.550 align:middle line:84%
a lot of them would say,
like, I feel it in my heart,

00:15:12.550 --> 00:15:14.930 align:middle line:90%
or I'm seeing, or I'm hearing.

00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:17.720 align:middle line:90%
And so I had so many questions.

00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:19.900 align:middle line:90%
So I started interviewing them.

00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:23.380 align:middle line:84%
And they would also
mention in the readings,

00:15:23.380 --> 00:15:24.880 align:middle line:84%
I forgot to mention
this, they would

00:15:24.880 --> 00:15:29.030 align:middle line:84%
mention reincarnation and
soul lessons and soul groups.

00:15:29.030 --> 00:15:31.350 align:middle line:90%
And I did not grow up spiritual.

00:15:31.350 --> 00:15:35.152 align:middle line:84%
I was not exposed to any kind
of spiritual philosophy--

00:15:35.152 --> 00:15:36.110 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Any religion?

00:15:36.110 --> 00:15:39.770 align:middle line:84%
>>SOBHANI: --or religion,
really, and especially not one

00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:41.070 align:middle line:90%
that included reincarnation.

00:15:41.070 --> 00:15:43.890 align:middle line:84%
So whenever they would say
those things in the readings,

00:15:43.890 --> 00:15:46.890 align:middle line:84%
I would just zone out, and
it would go over my head.

00:15:46.890 --> 00:15:49.320 align:middle line:84%
But like I said, I recorded
them and wrote it down.

00:15:49.320 --> 00:15:52.070 align:middle line:84%
I just didn't know what to
do with that information.

00:15:52.070 --> 00:15:57.150 align:middle line:84%
And so when I started talking
to them and then reading,

00:15:57.150 --> 00:15:59.580 align:middle line:90%
then a picture started to form.

00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:01.680 align:middle line:90%
And I got curious about that.

00:16:01.680 --> 00:16:03.770 align:middle line:84%
It started to land
in my head as,

00:16:03.770 --> 00:16:05.790 align:middle line:84%
like, maybe I should
look at this next.

00:16:05.790 --> 00:16:09.020 align:middle line:84%
And I also started to interview
my scientist colleagues

00:16:09.020 --> 00:16:10.870 align:middle line:90%
because I started to feel crazy.

00:16:10.870 --> 00:16:11.670 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:16:11.670 --> 00:16:14.070 align:middle line:84%
This is really the wonderful
part of your story,

